因自炎性疾病或<i>MYD88</i> L265p突变有关的任何病理变异。他符合SCHS的诊断标准，并接受了硼替佐米治疗，从而显着改善临床症状和IGMκ单克隆蛋白水平的下降。患者可以很好地容忍治疗。该病例表明，除了抗IL-1疗法和布鲁顿酪氨酸激酶（BTK）抑制剂外，硼替佐米可以被视为SCHS的潜在治疗选择。</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID： <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935483/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">39935483</a> | PMC： <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11810973/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11810973</a> | doi： <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1520470>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1520470</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> PubMed：39935483</guid><pubDate> Wed, 12 Feb 2025 06:00:00 -0500</pubDate><dc:creator> Hua Bai</dc:creator><dc:creator> Dongming Zhou</dc:creator><dc:creator> Jinwen Liu</dc:creator><dc:creator> Jie He</dc:creator><dc:creator>周敏</dc:creator><dc:creator>Wenyong粉丝</dc:creator><dc:creator>Bing Chen</dc:creator><dc:creator>杨Xu</dc:creator><dc:date> 2025-02-12</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>病例报告：在患有施尼兹勒综合征患者的硼替佐米的治疗用途</dc:title><dc:identifier>PMID：39935483</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> PMC：PMC11810973</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1520470</dc:identifier></item><item><title>年龄影响小儿败血症的循环免疫特征</title><link/>https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935482/?utm_source=Chrome&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=journals&amp;utm_content=101560960&amp;fc=None&amp;ff=20250212091005&amp;v=2.18.0.post9+e462414<description>结论：调节性T细胞衰竭可能导致小儿脓毒症的发病机理。年龄是影响败血症相关的免疫失调和周围循环中的记忆T细胞的重要变量，仅败血症与年龄相关。 </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><p style="color: #4aa564;"><b>前免疫</b>。 2025年1月28日； 16：1527142。 doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1527142。环保2025。</p><p><b>抽象的</b></p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">背景：随着患者的年龄，免疫反应的变化，但是对败血症的免疫失调的研究通常不会将年龄视为关键变量。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">目的：我们假设年龄会影响化脓性儿童的免疫反应，并且健康儿童和患有败血症，不复杂感染或急性器官功能障碍的健康儿童和儿童免疫特征的不同。我们表征了向我们的三级护理儿童医院出示的儿童的循环免疫力。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">方法：这项调查是一项前瞻性的，观察性的研究，该研究从2020年7月至2022年9月开始招募患者。如果患者小于21岁，被PICU录取并接受了液体复苏和抗生素。从PICU第1天收集的样品中分离出外周血单核细胞。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">结果：八十名患者被招募。患有败血症的儿童具有更多的调节性CD4 <sup>+</sup> T细胞和记忆CD4 <sup>+</sup> T细胞，CD4 <sup>+</sup> IL-10 <sup>+</sup>和CD8 <sup>+</sup> T-bet <sup>+</sup> T细胞的含量较少。<i>离体</i>刺激后，败血症样品的CD4 <sup>+</sup> T细胞降低了IL-10的降低，而不是健康对照。记忆CD4 <sup>+</sup> T细胞和调节性CD4 <sup>+</sup> T细胞仅在败血症中与年龄呈正相关。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">结论：调节性T细胞衰竭可能导致小儿脓毒症的发病机理。年龄是影响败血症相关的免疫失调和周围循环中的记忆T细胞的重要变量，仅败血症与年龄相关。</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID： <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935482/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">39935482</a> | PMC： <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11810941/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11810941</a> | doi： <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1527142>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1527142</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> PubMed：39935482</guid><pubDate> Wed, 12 Feb 2025 06:00:00 -0500</pubDate><dc:creator>格蕾丝·菲斯勒（Grace Fisler）</dc:creator><dc:creator> Mariana R Brewer</dc:creator><dc:creator>奥马尔·亚彭（Omar Yaipen）</dc:creator><dc:creator>克利福德（Clifford）的德意志人</dc:creator><dc:creator>马修·泰勒（Matthew D Taylor）</dc:creator><dc:date> 2025-02-12</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>年龄影响小儿败血症的循环免疫特征</dc:title><dc:identifier>PMID：39935482</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> PMC：PMC11810941</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1527142</dc:identifier></item><item><title> IL-33信号传导对于IL-10诱导的食物过敏过程中肥大细胞反应增强的增强是可分配的</title><link/>https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935481/?utm_source=Chrome&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=journals&amp;utm_content=101560960&amp;fc=None&amp;ff=20250212091005&amp;v=2.18.0.post9+e462414<description>结论：我们的数据表明，IL-10可以增强WT和ST2^（ - / - ）小鼠的MC反应，进一步证实了其对MCS的促炎作用，并表明它们不受IL-33信号传导的调节。 </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><p style="color: #4aa564;"><b>前免疫</b>。 2025年1月28日； 16：1526498。 doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1526498。环保2025。</p><p><b>抽象的</b></p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">背景：IL-33/ST2轴在食物过敏过程中在IgE介导的肥大细胞（MC）反应的发展中起关键作用。我们最近证明，多效性细胞因子IL-10不仅对IgE介导的MC激活产生促炎作用，而且还促进了IL-33诱导的MC反应。但是，尚未检查IL-33对于IL-10的促炎作用是否必要。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">方法：因此，为了确定IL-33/ST2轴在该途径中的作用，我们评估了IL-10对野生型（WT）和ST2 <sup>- / -</sup>小鼠IgE介导的MC激活和食物过敏发展的影响。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">结果：IL-10刺激显着增强了IL-33基因表达，ST2受体表达，细胞因子产生，MMCP-1分泌以及来自WT小鼠的IgE和抗原激活的骨髓衍生的MC（BMMC）的IL-10刺激。 ST2 <sup>- / -</sup> BMMC响应IgE依赖性激活而表现出降低的细胞因子分泌。但是，IL-10也增强了这些细胞中细胞因子的产生，MMCP-1分泌和增殖。为了进一步评估IL-10的作用，在WT和ST2 <sup>- / -</sup>小鼠中诱导食物过敏，受到抗体介导的IL-10耗竭。 IL-10耗尽的WT小鼠在MC介导的OVA挑战的反应中表现出明显的衰减。 While ST2 <sup>-/-</sup> mice also exhibited a profound suppression of MC responses, IL-10 depletion had no additional effects.但是，与ST2 <sup>- / -</sup>小鼠相比，ST2 <sup>- / -</sup> /IL-10 <sup>- / -</sup>小鼠在OVA-Ige和抗原特异性MC激活中表现出进一步降低。 </p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one">结论：我们的数据表明，IL-10可以增强WT和ST2 <sup>- / -</sup>小鼠的MC响应，进一步证实了其对MC的促炎作用，并表明它们不受IL-33信号传导的调节。</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID： <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935481/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">39935481</a> | PMC： <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11810977/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11810977</a> | doi： <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1526498>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1526498</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> PubMed：39935481</guid><pubDate> Wed, 12 Feb 2025 06:00:00 -0500</pubDate><dc:creator> Dylan Krajewski</dc:creator><dc:creator> Saurav Ranjitkar</dc:creator><dc:creator>内森·乔丹（Nathan Jordan）</dc:creator><dc:creator> Sallie S Schneider</dc:creator><dc:creator>克林顿B马西亚斯</dc:creator><dc:date>2025-02-12</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>IL-33信号传导对于IL-10诱导的食物过敏过程中肥大细胞反应增强的增强是可分配的</dc:title><dc:identifier>PMID：39935481</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> PMC：PMC11810977</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi：10.3389/fimmu.2025.1526498</dc:identifier></item><item><title> &lt;em>;In silico&lt;/em>; design of a multi-epitope vaccine against &lt;em>;Mycobacterium avium&lt;/em>; subspecies &lt;em>;paratuberculosis&lt;/em>;</title><link/> https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935480/?utm_source=Chrome&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=journals&amp;utm_content=101560960&amp;fc=None&amp;ff=20250212091005&amp;v=2.18.0.post9+e462414<description> The widespread chronic enteritis known as Paratuberculosis (PTB) or Johne&#39;s disease (JD) is caused by Mycobacterium avium subspecies paratuberculosis (MAP), posing a significant threat to global public health. Given the challenges associated with PTB or JD, the development and application of vaccines are potentially important for disease control. The aim of this study was to design a multi-epitope vaccine against MAP. A total of 198 MAP genomes were analyzed using pan-genome and reverse... </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><p style="color: #4aa564;"><b>前免疫</b>。 2025 Jan 28;16:1505313. doi: 10.3389/fimmu.2025.1505313.环保2025。</p><p><b>抽象的</b></p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one"> The widespread chronic enteritis known as Paratuberculosis (PTB) or Johne&#39;s disease (JD) is caused by <i>Mycobacterium avium</i> subspecies <i>paratuberculosis</i> (MAP), posing a significant threat to global public health. Given the challenges associated with PTB or JD, the development and application of vaccines are potentially important for disease control. The aim of this study was to design a multi-epitope vaccine against MAP. A total of 198 MAP genomes were analyzed using pan-genome and reverse vaccinology approaches. B-cell and T-cell epitope analysis was performed on the selected promising cross-protective antigens followed by selection of epitopes with high antigenicity, no allergenicity, and no toxicity for the design of the vaccine. The designed vaccine was evaluated through molecular dynamics simulations, molecular docking, and immunological simulations. The results revealed the identification of five promising cross-protective antigens. In total, 10 B-cell epitopes, 10 HTL epitopes, and 9 CTL epitopes were selected for the design of the vaccine. Both the vaccine candidate and the vaccine-TLR4 complex demonstrated considerable stability in molecular dynamics simulations. Molecular docking studies confirmed that the vaccine candidate successfully interacted with TLR4. Immunological simulations showed an increase in both B-cell and T-cell populations after vaccination. Additionally, the vaccine candidate exhibited a codon adaptability index of 1.0 and a GC content of 53.64%, indicating strong potential for successful expression in <i>Escherichia coli</i> . This research developed a multi-epitope vaccine targeting MAP through pan-genomes and reverse vaccinology methods, offering innovative strategies for creating effective vaccines against MAP.</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID: <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935480/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">39935480</a> | PMC: <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11810964/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11810964</a> | DOI: <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1505313>10.3389/fimmu.2025.1505313</a></p></div> ]]>;</content:encoded><guid ispermalink="false"> pubmed:39935480</guid><pubDate> Wed, 12 Feb 2025 06:00:00 -0500</pubDate><dc:creator> Weiqi Guo</dc:creator><dc:creator> Xinyu Wang</dc:creator><dc:creator> Jiangang Hu</dc:creator><dc:creator> Beibei Zhang</dc:creator><dc:creator> Luru Zhao</dc:creator><dc:creator> Guangdong Zhang</dc:creator><dc:creator> Jingjing Qi</dc:creator><dc:creator> Zuzhang Wei</dc:creator><dc:creator> Yanqing Bao</dc:creator><dc:creator> Mingxing Tian</dc:creator><dc:creator> Shaohui Wang</dc:creator><dc:date> 2025-02-12</dc:date><dc:source>免疫学领域</dc:source><dc:title>&lt;em>;In silico&lt;/em>; design of a multi-epitope vaccine against &lt;em>;Mycobacterium avium&lt;/em>; subspecies &lt;em>;paratuberculosis&lt;/em>;</dc:title><dc:identifier> pmid:39935480</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> pmc:PMC11810964</dc:identifier><dc:identifier> doi:10.3389/fimmu.2025.1505313</dc:identifier></item><item><title> Castleman disease misdiagnosed as immunoglobulin G4-related disease: a case report</title><link/> https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935479/?utm_source=Chrome&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=journals&amp;utm_content=101560960&amp;fc=None&amp;ff=20250212091005&amp;v=2.18.0.post9+e462414<description> Castleman disease (CD) and immunoglobulin G4-related disease (IgG4-RD) are rare systemic immune-mediated disorders that share overlapping clinical features, posing significant challenges in differential diagnosis. Here, we present a case of generalized lymphadenopathy initially misdiagnosed as IgG4-RD, which demonstrated a poor response to hormonal therapy. Subsequent pathological biopsy and immunohistochemical analysis ultimately confirmed the diagnosis of CD. This case underscores the... </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><p style="color: #4aa564;"><b>前免疫</b>。 2025 Jan 28;16:1532627. doi: 10.3389/fimmu.2025.1532627.环保2025。</p><p><b>抽象的</b></p><p xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:p1="http://pubmed.gov/pub-one"> Castleman disease (CD) and immunoglobulin G4-related disease (IgG4-RD) are rare systemic immune-mediated disorders that share overlapping clinical features, posing significant challenges in differential diagnosis. Here, we present a case of generalized lymphadenopathy initially misdiagnosed as IgG4-RD, which demonstrated a poor response to hormonal therapy. Subsequent pathological biopsy and immunohistochemical analysis ultimately confirmed the diagnosis of CD. This case underscores the limitations of relying solely on serum IgG4 levels as a diagnostic marker to distinguish CD from IgG4-RD. Comprehensive evaluation, including clinical presentation, organ involvement, serological and pathological findings, as well as therapeutic response, is essential to ensure accurate diagnosis and timely management.</p><p style="color: lightgray"> PMID: <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39935479/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">39935479</a> | PMC: <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/PMC11810934/?utm_source=Chrome&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=journals&utm_content=101560960&ff=20250212091005&v=2.18.0.post9+e462414">PMC11810934</a> | DOI: <a href=https://doi.org/10.3389/fimmu.2025.1532627>10